      {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12905391/comment/15301482",
        "id": "15301482",
        "author": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rkanter",
          "name": "rkanter",
          "key": "rkanter",
          "avatarUrls": {
            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
          },
          "displayName": "Robert Kanter",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
        },
        "body": "[~rmohan], I think you're mixing up the disk checker with the health checker.  The {{NodeHealthCheckerService}} class reports a node's health based on two other classes: {{NodeHealthScriptRunner}} and {{LocalDirsHandlerService}}.  {{NodeHealthScriptRunner}} is for checking the general health of a node and is pluggable.  In fact, it has no default implementation, the user must provide a script to run.  The script can return that either the node is healthy or not healthy.  {{LocalDirsHandlerService}} is for checking the health of the local directories on each disk that are used for Containers.  It is not currently pluggable (YARN-5137 aims to change this), but does have deeper integration for the NM.  For instance, the NM can continue operating in some capacity by no longer giving bad disks to newly allocated Containers.  \n\nSo, I actually think we should be closing this JIRA (YARN-4271) as \"Invalid\" given that the health checker is already pluggable, and reopen YARN-5137 because the disk checker is not.\n\nDoes that make sense?",
        "updateAuthor": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rkanter",
          "name": "rkanter",
          "key": "rkanter",
          "avatarUrls": {
            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
          },
          "displayName": "Robert Kanter",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
        },
        "created": "2016-05-26T03:53:26.626+0000",
        "updated": "2016-05-26T03:53:26.626+0000"
      },
      {
