          "displayName": "Karthik Kambatla",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
        },
        "body": "As I see things, YARN-5137 and this JIRA are slightly different. \n\nYARN-5137 has a smaller scope of improving on the existing disk checks by making them pluggable. If I squint enough, YARN-5137 is required for this. And, if this were an umbrella JIRA, may be even be a part of this. \n\n[~rmohan] - am I right in my understanding that this is a much larger scope? In this context (cloud environments), how does disk health affect node health? Is it okay for a few disks to be broken? Are these disks used for local directories by YARN? ",
